history.content:
Upper division CS courses will move students from the waitlist into the class as the # of ta's hired allows us to support teaching more students.  That is in the process of happening across the upper division and we won't be able to answer specific questions about specific courses. You'll know hiring has happened when the class expands.

Everyone not enrolled in a class needs a backup plan unless not having any class to fulfill a particular requirement that the waitlisted course might fulfill would not hamper your ability to graduate on time with your degree.
